- Call `drop_warmup_nans(df, list(feature_metadata.keys()))` to remove
  the initial rows where rolling features haven't accumulated enough
  history. Print the number of rows dropped and the new date range.
- After warm-up removal, save the clean feature DataFrame as
  `data/interim/features_pre_cv.parquet` and the metadata dict as
  `data/interim/feature_metadata.json`. These are the inputs to
  Block 5 (econometrics) in the next phase.
- Display `df.head()` showing the first few rows of the feature matrix.
- The markdown cell above should explain: `b_features.py` applies a
  Universal Lag Rule — all rolling/expanding features are shifted by 1
  day (`.shift(1)`) to prevent look-ahead bias, except cyclical
  calendar features and deterministic event counters (days since halving)
